# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Responsible AI-Assisted Research — .gitignore
#
# Principle (see CLAUDE.md): raw data is immutable truth and IS tracked here
# (pwt110.dta is small + public). Everything a machine can REBUILD is ignored,
# so the repository only ever contains inputs, code, and code-emitted outputs.
# For your own project, keep large or private raw data OUT of git and document
# how to download it instead (see data/raw/README.md).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Derived / intermediate data — rebuilt by `python code/run_all.py`.
# Ignore the contents but keep the folder + its README on a fresh clone.
data/derived/*
!data/derived/README.md

# Secrets & credentials — NEVER commit these
.env
*.key
*.pem
credentials.*

# LaTeX build artifacts (the PDF is built by CI and by Overleaf, not committed)
*.aux
*.bbl
*.blg
*.log
*.out
*.toc
*.fls
*.fdb_latexmk
*.synctex.gz
*.run.xml
*-blx.bib
manuscript.pdf

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.venv/
venv/
.ipynb_checkpoints/
*.egg-info/

# OS / editor cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
